Contrary to the above mentioned studies Zhou et al comparing survivors and non‐survivors in a cohort of 191 patients from two hospitals in Wuhan, found that, despite more frequent in non‐survivors (46% vs 1%; 
 P < .001), hs‐cTnI >28 pg/mL was not associated with mortality in multivariate analysis. Even though, it is remarkable that this study was unpowered to draw conclusions from this analysis due to the excess of variable for only 54 events.

